cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a two-phase cellular-based mMTC network, which involves data transmission and resource scheduling among MTDs. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry to develop a tractable analytical framework to investigate the signal-to-interference ratio (SIR) for each phase. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers scheduling schemes for resource allocation among MTDs, which is a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of massive amounts of data from MTDs, which can include multimedia content. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves the aggregation of data from multiple MTDs, which requires efficient data structures and algorithms.
